        <h3>About Gedu College of Business Studies</h3>
        <p>
       Gedu College of Business Studies is accredited ‚ÄòB+‚Äô by Bhutan Accreditation Council. GCBS is the Premier College under Royal University of Bhutan that offered business and management courses in the country.
      </p>
      <p>
        Gedu College of Business Studies (GCBS) was established as a constituent college of the Royal University of Bhutan (RUB) in 2008 after the transfer of the Department of Commerce from Sherubtse College. 
        The college is located at Gedu, and it covers an area of 184.5 acres. The college campus was developed by Tala Hydroelectric Project Authority (THPA). 
        It is about a 48 km drive from Phuentsholing and 104 km from Thimphu.
      </p>
      <p>
        Besides an excellent team of both national and international faculty with impressive academic and industrial backgrounds, the college 
        is well equipped with accommodation facilities, guest rooms, IT labs, a library, cafeterias, and conference halls. It also has an indoor 
        sports complex where students can play games such as futsal, basketball, table tennis, and badminton.
      </p>
      
